<subSubSection id="C31D9BBDFF8BFFED5011F92600214AC2" pageId="16" pageNumber="243" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB8C836FF8BFFED5011F92600214AC2" blockId="16.[332,1280,902,1775]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="B9731424FF8BFFED5011F92602F94A83" bold="true" box="[332,460,1687,1711]" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is dedicated to Alexander Riedel (Karlsruhe, 
<collectingCountry id="F31088A6FF8BFFED5507F926078A4A83" box="[1114,1215,1687,1711]" name="Germany" pageId="16" pageNumber="243">Germany</collectingCountry>
) who significantly contributed to the knowledge of New Guinean beetles and collected most of the scaphidiines dealt in the present paper.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31D9BBDFF8AFFEC506DFE3801E14DCD" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB8C836FF8AFFEC506DFE3801E14DCD" blockId="17.[304,1251,393,481]" pageId="17" pageNumber="244">
